Oliver's hometown.

439
00:35:12,284 --> 00:35:15,549
Wait, I'm totally lost. You just said
that they're two different people.

440
00:35:15,621 --> 00:35:19,717
Yeah. Two people the same age
from the same small town!

441
00:35:19,792 --> 00:35:22,522
I looked it up.
It's a small town!

442
00:35:22,595 --> 00:35:24,893
Yeah, so what?

443
00:35:24,964 --> 00:35:27,524
Brooke, don't you think they would've
heard of each other, these guys?

444
00:35:27,600 --> 00:35:30,228
You know, growing up?
Gotten mixed up before?

445
00:35:30,302 --> 00:35:33,465
Oliver didn't say anything like that.
He just threw the letter away.

446
00:35:33,539 --> 00:35:35,473
- Well, wait a minute.
- So--

447
00:35:35,541 --> 00:35:38,203
There could be ten other Michael
Faradays in Northern Virginia.

448
00:35:38,277 --> 00:35:41,610
- You would never know that.
- So I called Kansas State.

449
00:35:41,681 --> 00:35:44,946
Here's what I'm saying.
Kansas State University...

450
00:35:45,017 --> 00:35:48,145
had no Oliver Lang on record,
from that year or any year.

451
00:35:48,220 --> 00:35:51,417
So either he didn't really
go to that school...

452
00:35:51,490 --> 00:35:54,050
or that's not his real name.

453
00:35:54,126 --> 00:35:57,857
