with whom in Washington?

599
00:49:03,081 --> 00:49:04,912
Thank you.

600
00:49:09,287 --> 00:49:11,346
Just run through this scenario with me.

601
00:49:11,423 --> 00:49:14,824
Theoretically,
why would someone do that?

602
00:49:14,893 --> 00:49:18,294
Do what? Change his name to the name
of a person who died the day before?

603
00:49:18,363 --> 00:49:21,821
Yeah. Someone the same age
from the same hometown.

604
00:49:21,900 --> 00:49:25,734
Why? Would it be to take over
that person's life?

605
00:49:25,804 --> 00:49:27,738
No, that wouldn't work.

606
00:49:27,806 --> 00:49:30,536
When you die, the death certificate
goes both state and federal.

607
00:49:30,609 --> 00:49:34,807
Driver's licenses, Social Security
numbers, they're voided.

608
00:49:34,880 --> 00:49:38,543
-Can't do it to hide the person you are.
-Then why would you do it?

609
00:49:38,617 --> 00:49:41,848
You'd do it to hide
the person you were.

610
00:49:41,920 --> 00:49:44,445
Say you wanted to find out...

611
00:49:44,523 --> 00:49:47,390
a criminal record for your guy
prior to the name change.

612
00:49:47,459 --> 00:49:51,395
- Unless you're a real professional--
- You'd check on the name he has now--

613
00:49:51,463 --> 00:49:54,455
And the records you'd find back then
would be for somebody else entirely.

614
00:49:54,533 --> 00:49:58,435
That's the significance of making
the change right after a person's death.

615
00:49:58,503 --> 00:50:02,837
- No overlap.
- It gives you a whole new history.

616
00:50:02,908 --> 00:50:05,172
It helps the old one disappear.

617
00:50:08,013 --> 00:50:10,481
Is there something you want
to tell me, Michael?

618
00:50:11,616 --> 00:50:16,349
Whit, it I give you a name,
