- Yeah, we disagree about politics.

732
00:59:51,095 --> 00:59:54,258
And Washington?
And Leah?

733
00:59:54,332 --> 00:59:56,300
- Do you remember this?
- Oh, my--

734
00:59:56,367 --> 00:59:58,699
The guy is testing me.

735
00:59:58,769 --> 01:00:02,136
He wants to see
it I'm an enemy or an ally.

736
01:00:03,241 --> 01:00:06,699
You are the one who brought up Leah.

737
01:00:06,777 --> 01:00:09,678
Is that what this is about?

738
01:00:09,747 --> 01:00:12,215
No, it's not about Leah!

739
01:00:16,120 --> 01:00:18,520
You know, this class...

740
01:00:18,589 --> 01:00:21,251
that you slave over...

741
01:00:21,325 --> 01:00:26,160
to carry on Leah's work,
to have something in her memory?

742
01:00:29,700 --> 01:00:33,363
You know,
plots and conspiracies...

743
01:00:33,437 --> 01:00:36,031
and red flags going up.

744
01:00:36,107 --> 01:00:39,133
Yeah, this is Leah's world now.

745
01:00:41,212 --> 01:00:42,804
I'm--

746
01:00:50,087 --> 01:00:51,679
I can't.

747
01:00:54,625 --> 01:00:57,059
Listen, I know...

748
01:00:57,128 --> 01:01:00,655
that he's changed his name--

749
01:01:00,731 --> 01:01:03,359
- Stop it, for me.
- He lived in St Louis...

750
01:01:03,434 --> 01:01:06,232
when the bombs were goin' off.

751
01:01:06,304 --> 01:01:09,740
He's working on this building
that he doesn't want me to see.

752
01:01:14,178 --> 01:01:16,112
I don't think
I can stay here tonight.

753
01:01:17,748 --> 01:01:20,273
I'm not staying.

754
01:02:34,258 --> 01:02:36,488
Never did like that picture.

755
01:02:39,330 --> 01:02:41,264
You know me, Michael?

756
01:02:42,333 --> 01:02:44,301
You think you know me?

757
01:02:45,903 --> 01:02:48,872
Yeah, you know me better
than I know myself, don't you?

758
01:02:49,874 --> 01:02:52,342
Kansas City Star.
I saw you.

759
01:02:52,410 --> 01:02:55,038
You wanna tell me something
I don't know?

760
01:02:56,514 --> 01:02:59,950
- I know what I read.
- You know a 16-year-old kid.

761
01:03:02,053 --> 01:03:04,078
You don't know me.

762
01:03:04,155 --> 01:03:06,316
You know a kid at 16.

763
01:03:09,560 --> 01:03:12,028
Damn you!
You've been a guest in my house!

764
01:03:12,096 --> 01:03:14,894
You're a guest in mine, Fenimore.

765
01:03:16,000 --> 01:03:18,730
Bill, Will, William--
What do I call you?

766
01:03:18,803 --> 01:03:22,830
Who the hell do you think you are
judging me? What gives you the right?

767
01:03:26,177 --> 01:03:28,145
You ever worked on a farm?

768
01:03:33,217 --> 01:03:35,811
Make your living,
support your family?

769
01:03:37,321 --> 01:03:43,191
The government stole my father's water--
a stream running through our land.

770
01:03:43,260 --> 01:03:45,854
Said they were appropriating it
for other uses.

771
01:03:47,465 --> 01:03:51,561
We couldn't grow crops,
we couldn't raise cattle.

772
01:03:51,635 --> 01:03:54,069
We had loans we couldn't pay.

773
01:03:56,006 --> 01:03:57,940
My father woke up one mornin'...

774
01:03:58,008 --> 01:04:01,500
and he realized
he was worth more dead than alive.

775
01:04:03,047 --> 01:04:05,709
His skin and bones...

776
01:04:05,783 --> 01:04:08,581
were worth more
in insurance money...

777
01:04:08,652 --> 01:04:10,950
than as a damn farmer.

778
01:04:13,758 --> 01:04:16,693
I found his tractor...

779
01:04:16,761 --> 01:04:19,730
at the bottom of the bluffs
behind our house.

780
01:04:19,797 --> 01:04:21,731
He made it look like an accident.

781
01:04:21,799 --> 01:04:26,759
I found his body.
And the note?

782
01:04:29,006 --> 01:04:30,997
He wrote it to me.

783
01:04:37,047 --> 01:04:39,811
Insurance money paid off
what Mom could...

784
01:04:39,884 --> 01:04:42,478
but it wasn't enough.

785
01:04:43,554 --> 01:04:47,718
Neighbors--
Neighbors took our land at auction.

786
01:04:49,293 --> 01:04:52,956
All because some bureaucrat
stuck a pin in a map...

787
01:04:54,665 --> 01:04:58,465
in some creek in the middle of Kansas,
said we couldn't use our own water.

788
01:04:58,536 --> 01:05:00,470
Doesn't give you the right
to build a bomb.

789
01:05:00,538 --> 01:05:04,201
I was sixteen.
Sixteen!

790
01:05:04,275 --> 01:05:07,369
You ever do anything wrong
when you were 16?

791
01:05:08,612 --> 01:05:10,944
You ever crash your car?

792
01:05:11,015 --> 01:05:15,714
You ever, uh, steal anything?
You ever screw the wrong girl?

793
01:05:15,786 --> 01:05:18,448
You gonna tell your kid everything
you did when you were 16?

794
01:05:18,522 --> 01:05:21,184
The lies you told?
The drugs you took?

795
01:05:23,160 --> 01:05:25,094
I've been judged for this!

796
01:05:25,162 --> 01:05:29,826
I got sent away for it, and it was
the best thing that ever happened to me.

797
01:05:29,900 --> 01:05:31,834
The best thing.

798
01:05:38,609 --> 01:05:40,201
Who's Oliver?

799
01:05:48,419 --> 01:05:50,751
He was my best friend growin' up.

800
01:05:53,924 --> 01:05:56,654
He died when we were both 25.

801
01:05:59,163 --> 01:06:01,097
I did it to honor him...

802
01:06:03,334 --> 01:06:05,268
to carry on his name.

803
01:06:07,271 --> 01:06:09,205
And to hide.

804
01:06:10,674 --> 01:06:12,608
Yeah, to hide.

805
01:06:14,211 --> 01:06:17,738
I didn't want any son I had
knowing what I did.

806
01:06:19,950 --> 01:06:23,511
I didn't want my kids
to be burdened...

807
01:06:23,587 --> 01:06:26,647
with people looking through
old newspapers.

808
01:06:28,993 --> 01:06:31,655
I'm not proud of this.

809
01:06:33,964 --> 01:06:35,989
This isn't pride.

810
01:06:38,402 --> 01:06:41,030
I wish it never happened.

811
01:06:42,940 --> 01:06:46,501
You know, I wish to God...

812
01:06:46,577 --> 01:06:49,307
that my family could have...

813
01:06:49,380 --> 01:06:52,042
my father's good name.

814
01:06:57,655 --> 01:07:00,783
You know, you have a right
to know who lives next door...

815
01:07:00,858 --> 01:07:05,591
who talks to your kid,
who considers himself your friend.

816
01:07:07,231 --> 01:07:09,927
But you also have the right--

817
01:07:10,000 --> 01:07:13,060
It you have a problem with me,
it you have issues with me...

818
01:07:14,939 --> 01:07:18,375
you could have the decency
to walk across the street...

819
01:07:18,442 --> 01:07:21,104
and tell me to my face.

820
01:11:29,793 --> 01:11:32,557
Hi, this is Michael.
Leave a message.

821
01:11:32,629 --> 01:11:34,927
It's me. Listen.

822
01:11:34,998 --> 01:11:38,297
I think you're right.
I saw Oliver...

823
01:11:38,368 --> 01:11:41,997
at the mall in the garage.

824
01:11:42,072 --> 01:11:45,803
He switched cars with somebody,
and I followed him...

825
01:11:45,876 --> 01:11:48,140
to this warehouse delivery place.

826
01:11:50,380 --> 01:11:54,680
They were unloading
these long, metal boxes.

827
01:11:56,720 --> 01:12:01,157
I want to talk to you.
I'm coming over, okay?

828
01:12:09,566 --> 01:12:11,261
I knew it was you.

829
01:12:17,407 --> 01:12:19,341
What are you doing here?

830
01:12:22,613 --> 01:12:26,606
Just shopping.
What are you doing here?

831
01:12:28,685 --> 01:12:30,277
Shopping.

832
01:12:33,724 --> 01:12:35,521
Great.

833
01:12:35,592 --> 01:12:37,184
Yeah.

834
01:12:56,580 --> 01:13:00,380
They say a man was shot several times
while driving along 19th street.

835
01:13:00,450 --> 01:13:04,181
The car struck several other vehicles
before slamming into a tree.

836
01:13:04,254 --> 01:13:07,382
The victim was pronounced
dead at the scene.

837
01:13:07,457 --> 01:13:09,618
Elsewhere, a single-car accident
near Reston is tying up...

838
01:13:09,693 --> 01:13:12,753
evening traffic on westbound
Route 7 at this hour.

839
01:13:12,829 --> 01:13:15,559
Details are sketchy at this point.
What we can tell you...

840
01:13:15,632 --> 01:13:17,862
from our overhead shot is that
the accident took place...

841
01:13:17,935 --> 01:13:20,130
near the Pine Glenn Outlet Center.

842
01:13:20,203 --> 01:13:22,501
No other vehicles appear to be
involved in what police say...

843
01:13:22,572 --> 01:13:24,164
is a fatal crash.

844
01:13:24,241 --> 01:13:27,768
We'll have more information for you
when it becomes available.

845
01:13:30,013 --> 01:13:32,777
The driver of the car, described
as a woman in her mid-20s...

846
01:13:32,849 --> 01:13:34,817
has been pronounced dead
at the scene.

847
01:13:34,885 --> 01:13:38,412
Police say it appears she lost control
of the light blue 1989 Mustang...

848
01:13:38,488 --> 01:13:41,116
and crashed through a guardrail
along the ravine.

849
01:13:41,191 --> 01:13:44,683
Investigators believe
she was killed upon impact--

850
01:14:04,648 --> 01:14:06,775
Sir, you can't go down there.

851
01:14:06,850 --> 01:14:09,148
Sir, you can't come down here.

852
01:14:09,219 --> 01:14:11,119
- You can't go down there.
- Where is she?

853
01:14:14,024 --> 01:14:16,049
- She's gone sir. Been taken away.
- Where?

854
01:14:19,296 --> 01:14:21,560
- She's gone.
- Where?

855
01:14:21,631 --> 01:14:23,223
I'm sorry.

856
01:15:04,908 --> 01:15:06,773
Hey, General,
how you holding up?

857
01:15:06,843 --> 01:15:09,403
You wouldn't believe it!
It's so cool.

858
01:15:09,479 --> 01:15:12,710
We went swimming and climbing, and
one night there was a lightning storm.

859
01:15:12,783 --> 01:15:15,775
- We had to stay in a motel!
- You did?

860
01:15:15,852 --> 01:15:19,253
I learned how to make campfires,
and there's lots of knives.

861
01:15:19,322 --> 01:15:23,224
- Me and Brady can tell animal tracks.
- That's terrific.

862
01:15:23,293 --> 01:15:25,693
I've gotta go.
Troop Master's calling us.

863
01:15:25,762 --> 01:15:28,230
- We're doing a hike!
- Okay. Grant?

864
01:15:28,298 --> 01:15:30,858
I'll see you in a couple of days.
I love you.

865
01:15:30,934 --> 01:15:32,799
- I gotta go!
- Grant?

866
01:15:42,512 --> 01:15:45,538
It's better to tell him
when he gets back.

867
01:15:52,656 --> 01:15:54,624
Thanks for coming to get me.

868
01:15:54,691 --> 01:15:58,593
If there's anything you need...

869
01:15:58,662 --> 01:16:00,687
we're here.

870
01:16:00,764 --> 01:16:04,222
No, I won't.
I'll be tine.

871
01:16:07,237 --> 01:16:10,502
Don't let yourself-- I mean, sometimes
it's better not to be alone...

872
01:16:10,574 --> 01:16:12,542
when you don't have to be.

873
01:16:12,609 --> 01:16:14,543
She was a good person.

874
01:16:16,413 --> 01:16:19,348
Kind, kind girl.

875
01:16:19,416 --> 01:16:21,145
You know, it l--

876
01:16:21,218 --> 01:16:24,210
It I haven't been myself
these past few weeks--

877
01:16:27,457 --> 01:16:29,857
I'm sorry, for everything.

878
01:16:31,161 --> 01:16:33,459
She liked you...

879
01:16:33,530 --> 01:16:35,794
and your family very much.

880
01:16:40,170 --> 01:16:43,367
We're here for you.
We really are.

881
01:17:15,939 --> 01:17:18,237
- Hello?
- Michael, it's Whit.

882
01:17:18,308 --> 01:17:20,640
Haven't heard back from you, man.

883
01:17:24,648 --> 01:17:26,980
My girlfriend, Brooke,
was killed Friday.

884
01:17:27,050 --> 01:17:30,850
- Oh, God. No.
- Yeah.

885
01:17:32,422 --> 01:17:34,356
Can I talk to you later?

886
01:17:34,424 --> 01:17:38,224
Yeah, sure, whenever.
I'm here at the office.

887
01:17:38,295 --> 01:17:39,887
Thanks.

888
01:17:56,780 --> 01:17:59,112
- Agent Carver.
- Whit?

889
01:17:59,182 --> 01:18:02,948
What did you mean,
you haven't heard back from me?

890
01:18:03,019 --> 01:18:06,250
The message I left on Friday.
I understand now.

891
01:18:06,323 --> 01:18:09,292
- It's all right.
- What message?

892
01:18:09,359 --> 01:18:11,953
Well, the one about
speaking to your class.

893
01:18:12,028 --> 01:18:17,193
I thought with some ground rules,
we could set some things straight.

894
01:18:17,267 --> 01:18:19,792
Wait, wait, wait.
You called me Friday?

895
01:18:19,869 --> 01:18:23,032
- You left a message?
- Yeah, at the house.

896
01:18:27,978 --> 01:18:30,412
When did you call?

897
01:18:30,480 --> 01:18:34,416
I don't know.
Around 4:00 or 5:00, maybe, on Friday.

898
01:18:38,888 --> 01:18:41,584
I didn't have any messages.

899
01:18:41,658 --> 01:18:44,252
For Christ's sakes,
you just found out about Brooke.

900
01:18:44,327 --> 01:18:48,593
No, I didn't have any messages.
I'll call you back.

901
01:18:57,374 --> 01:18:59,342
Whit, listen to me.

902
01:18:59,409 --> 01:19:01,934
I know you can't do anything for me
or get me information...

903
01:19:02,012 --> 01:19:03,673
but I can give you information.

904
01:19:03,747 --> 01:19:07,683
The other day when I was talking about
somebody trying to hide their history?

905
01:19:07,751 --> 01:19:11,847
I was talking about my neighbor.
Oliver Lang-- that's his name.

906
01:19:11,921 --> 01:19:14,355
He used to be--

907
01:19:14,424 --> 01:19:19,123
It used to be William Fenimore. Run it
through your system, see what you got.

908
01:19:19,195 --> 01:19:21,993
- Oliver Lang. You writing this down?
- All right, slow down.

909
01:19:22,065 --> 01:19:24,693
This guy has a history, damn it!
Will you run the name?

910
01:19:24,768 --> 01:19:27,236
- Wait. What's he done?
- It I'm right...

911
01:19:27,304 --> 01:19:30,034
there are other people who called
my house that day, not just you.

912
01:19:30,106 --> 01:19:32,336
Find out. You can do that.
Please.

913
01:19:32,409 --> 01:19:34,969
- I'll call you when I get back.
- Where the hell are you going?

914
01:19:35,045 --> 01:19:36,706
To get you proof.
Run the name, Whit.

915
01:20:25,395 --> 01:20:27,329
Was it hard to find me?

916
01:20:28,598 --> 01:20:31,066
You've moved several times.

917
01:20:31,134 --> 01:20:35,002
Your wife said that--
Your ex-wife said--

918
01:20:35,071 --> 01:20:38,199
People know whose father I am.

919
01:20:40,710 --> 01:20:45,044
Mister, I've been through
all this before.

920
01:20:45,115 --> 01:20:47,709
The government, the police...

921
01:20:49,486 --> 01:20:51,078
and writers.

922
01:20:53,656 --> 01:20:56,386
People wanted to believe
it was political...

923
01:20:56,459 --> 01:20:59,087
some conspiracy, some group.

924
01:20:59,162 --> 01:21:02,393
Happy and I did too.

925
01:21:02,465 --> 01:21:04,660
Dean was not a strong boy.

926
01:21:04,734 --> 01:21:07,202
He was impressionable...

927
01:21:07,270 --> 01:21:10,205
believed what friends
around him said.

928
01:21:10,273 --> 01:21:13,140
Well, why couldn't he be involved...

929
01:21:13,209 --> 01:21:15,734
with people who could set him up...

930
01:21:15,812 --> 01:21:18,337
talk him into even this?

931
01:21:21,251 --> 01:21:25,517
The FBl, the police,
found nothing.

932
01:21:27,257 --> 01:21:32,058
It was him alone.
They decided this.

933
01:21:32,128 --> 01:21:34,119
Sixty-three dead...

934
01:21:35,598 --> 01:21:37,691
over taxes.

935
01:21:39,202 --> 01:21:40,692
Dean alone.

936
01:21:40,770 --> 01:21:43,364
You don't believe that, do you?

937
01:21:45,141 --> 01:21:47,075
I've never believed that.

938
01:21:47,143 --> 01:21:50,544
Have you heard the name
Oliver Lang or William Fenimore?

939
01:21:50,613 --> 01:21:52,547
I've heard too many names.

940
01:21:52,615 --> 01:21:56,278
Your son, Dean, was an electrician.

941
01:21:56,352 --> 01:21:59,947
Maybe he was contracted for...

942
01:22:00,023 --> 01:22:03,322
or he worked on a project--

943
01:22:03,393 --> 01:22:06,988
All of this
was investigated, mister!

944
01:22:07,063 --> 01:22:10,089
His neighbors, his customers...

945
01:22:10,166 --> 01:22:12,293
kids he grew up with
months ago.

946
01:22:12,368 --> 01:22:15,599
Dr. Scobee, I'm sorry
for bringing this all back.

947
01:22:15,672 --> 01:22:17,606
It never goes away.

948
01:22:17,674 --> 01:22:20,575
I had to come here.
You've got to understand.

949
01:22:20,643 --> 01:22:22,611
I think I know a man
who knew your son.

950
01:22:22,679 --> 01:22:25,648
He's 41, a structural engineer.

951
01:22:25,715 --> 01:22:28,650
He's got a wife, three kids.
He has this--

952
01:22:28,718 --> 01:22:31,516
May I ask what makes you so sure...

953
01:22:31,588 --> 01:22:34,921
that this man of yours had anything
to do with what happened here?

954
01:22:34,991 --> 01:22:38,256
For the same reason you're sure
your son didn't do it alone!

955
01:22:38,328 --> 01:22:42,856
I know my son was not alone,
because 10 children died that day!

956
01:22:42,932 --> 01:22:46,766
The day care center in the Roosevelt,
he had to know it was there.

957
01:22:46,836 --> 01:22:49,464
My son would never have done
anything to harm children.

958
01:22:49,539 --> 01:22:51,769
Your son didn't have any children.

959
01:22:51,841 --> 01:22:53,741
No!

960
01:22:53,810 --> 01:22:57,405
But he did things for them.

961
01:22:57,480 --> 01:23:00,347
He sponsored boys
from city shelters.

962
01:23:00,416 --> 01:23:05,718
Discoverer Troops. He coached
boys' football when he had time.

963
01:23:05,788 --> 01:23:08,382
Wait. Discoverer Troops?

964
01:23:10,894 --> 01:23:13,158
They're like Boy Scouts,
but for young children.

965
01:23:18,368 --> 01:23:21,201
He was a grown-up chaperon.

966
01:23:21,271 --> 01:23:26,106
He'd take them camping,
go to their meetings.

967
01:23:26,175 --> 01:23:29,838
Teach them.
There he is.

968
01:23:29,913 --> 01:23:32,643
It must have been
on some weekend adventure.

969
01:23:35,885 --> 01:23:39,150
Dean was best with children.

970
01:24:01,678 --> 01:24:03,077
Airport.

971
01:24:05,114 --> 01:24:07,639
Faraday, Grant Faraday.
I'll be there in a few hours.

972
01:24:07,717 --> 01:24:11,175
Don't let him go anywhere.
I'm coming. Tell him I'm coming.

973
01:24:26,869 --> 01:24:31,897
I'm here to pick up my son.
I called earlier this afternoon.

974
01:24:31,975 --> 01:24:34,102
- My son !
- What was that troop, sir?

975
01:24:34,177 --> 01:24:36,771
Troop? I don't know what troop.

976
01:24:36,846 --> 01:24:39,246
He's from Reston.
Grant Faraday.

977
01:24:41,484 --> 01:24:43,475
- Where's my son?
- Faraday.

978
01:24:44,854 --> 01:24:46,412
He was taken home
this afternoon, sir.

979
01:24:46,489 --> 01:24:48,719
- No.
- His father called.

980
01:24:48,791 --> 01:24:51,385
No, no, wait.
I'm his father. I called.

981
01:24:51,461 --> 01:24:55,295
But you called twice, sir.

982
01:24:55,365 --> 01:24:58,266
You said that there had been
an accident at home?

983
01:24:58,334 --> 01:25:00,234
- A car accident?
- No!

984
01:25:00,303 --> 01:25:02,601
You asked to speak
with his troop master, sir.

985
01:25:02,672 --> 01:25:04,663
I'm his goddamn father!
That wasn't me.

986
01:25:04,774 --> 01:25:07,242
Here it is, sir.
He was driven home.

987
01:25:07,310 --> 01:25:10,802
- By who?
- His troop master, sir.

988
01:25:13,650 --> 01:25:17,643
- He and another boy.
- What other boy?

989
01:25:17,720 --> 01:25:19,688
Lang, Brady Lang.

990
01:25:20,990 --> 01:25:24,289
The troop master left
with both of them.

991
01:27:13,603 --> 01:27:17,232
You're doing it again. I thought
I told you to come to me...

992
01:27:17,306 --> 01:27:19,240
- if there's something you wanna know.
- Where's my son?

993
01:27:19,308 --> 01:27:21,242
He's with mine. They're safe.
Can I get you something?

994
01:27:21,310 --> 01:27:23,244
- I saved his life!
- Some punch? What's that?

995
01:27:23,312 --> 01:27:25,542
- Your son, I saved his life!
- Yes, yes.

996
01:27:25,615 --> 01:27:27,810
And that's why
you're still here with us.

997
01:27:27,884 --> 01:27:30,682
- And Brooke?
- Brooke got in the way.

998
01:27:30,753 --> 01:27:33,051
We're on a schedule.
It's nothing personal.

999
01:27:33,122 --> 01:27:35,852
What the hell have you done
with my son?

1000
01:27:35,925 --> 01:27:39,884
It you want to be his father,
you'll walk to your house...

1001
01:27:39,962 --> 01:27:43,193
sleep in your bed,
teach your classes and live your life.

1002
01:27:43,266 --> 01:27:46,099
What are you telling me?
How many people are you gonna kill?

1003
01:27:46,169 --> 01:27:49,764
Well, it I see
any strange cars on my street...

1004
01:27:49,839 --> 01:27:53,172
it you feel compelled to talk
to anyone-- a federal agent, perhaps--

1005
01:27:53,242 --> 01:27:56,268
then I imagine
we're just gonna kill one.

1006
01:27:56,345 --> 01:27:58,836
He's nine years old.

1007
01:27:58,915 --> 01:28:01,543
When will he be ten?

1008
01:28:04,587 --> 01:28:06,521
He's a good kid.

1009
01:28:06,589 --> 01:28:08,557
A strong kid.

1010
01:28:08,624 --> 01:28:12,617
Reminds me of a boy I grew up with.
Maybe you've heard of him.

1011
01:28:12,695 --> 01:28:16,096
Oliver Lang?

1012
01:28:16,165 --> 01:28:18,793
I found him in the woods one day.

1013
01:28:18,868 --> 01:28:21,860
I would hate for Grant
to see the same for you.

1014
01:28:21,938 --> 01:28:25,772
- You sick fuck!
- You're the sick fuck!

1015
01:28:33,616 --> 01:28:35,550
I promise you, Michael.

1016
01:28:37,887 --> 01:28:41,118
It you stay a good neighbor,
and you are a good a neighbor...

1017
01:28:43,259 --> 01:28:45,193
you'll have him back.

1018
01:28:45,261 --> 01:28:50,392
But it you don't calm down, I don't know
that I can guarantee his safety.

1019
01:28:52,034 --> 01:28:55,401
- This will all be over in a few days.
- When?

1020
01:28:55,471 --> 01:28:58,963
- You're not in any danger.
- When? Tell me.

1021
01:29:02,378 --> 01:29:03,970
Please.

1022
01:29:06,182 --> 01:29:08,480
Because of you, my son is alive.

1023
01:29:10,653 --> 01:29:13,451
I would like very much
to return the favor.

1024
01:29:16,092 --> 01:29:18,151
Now...

1025
01:29:18,227 --> 01:29:20,161
we're having a party.

1026
01:29:22,598 --> 01:29:25,692
You're more than welcome to stay.

1027
01:30:33,035 --> 01:30:35,230
You're a hard man to find.

1028
01:30:35,304 --> 01:30:37,568
What are you, uh--

1029
01:30:37,640 --> 01:30:42,543
Your assistant told me you've been
taking long walks between classes.

1030
01:30:42,611 --> 01:30:45,239
Yeah, I can't talk to you now.

1031
01:30:45,314 --> 01:30:48,112
No? Can you talk to me ever?

1032
01:30:49,986 --> 01:30:52,580
You look like shit.
What's going on?

1033
01:30:55,992 --> 01:30:59,359
- I'm here about Oliver Lang.
- I gotta get to my class.

1034
01:30:59,428 --> 01:31:02,955
Well, how about
you teach me something?

1035
01:31:03,032 --> 01:31:06,559
Oliver Lang,
formerly William Fenimore.

1036
01:31:06,635 --> 01:31:09,536
We gave him a good look
after the St. Louis thing.

1037
01:31:09,605 --> 01:31:13,132
Everybody who ever used a bomb
got a good look.

1038
01:31:13,209 --> 01:31:15,143
His name change was legal.

1039
01:31:15,211 --> 01:31:18,305
We ran his social security number
through the National Crime Center.

1040
01:31:18,381 --> 01:31:22,681
Not a mark on his record ever since.
Him and everyone he knew came up clean.

1041
01:31:27,556 --> 01:31:29,990
That's what you found out about, huh?

1042
01:31:32,194 --> 01:31:36,358
Yeah, that Wichita shit back when
he was 16 got you thinking, huh?

1043
01:31:36,432 --> 01:31:40,300
Do you have something new on him
or do you just not like him...

1044
01:31:40,369 --> 01:31:41,893
in your neighborhood?

1045
01:31:41,971 --> 01:31:46,533
'Cause if this is all you got, then
you need to stop teaching that class...

1046
01:31:46,609 --> 01:31:48,634
'cause it's gettin' inside your head.

1047
01:31:48,711 --> 01:31:52,112
You tell me you got something
to go on and I'll go...

1048
01:31:52,181 --> 01:31:55,241
but I'm not gonna walk into another
Copper Creek, and neither should you.

1049
01:31:55,317 --> 01:31:59,651
I got nothing.
I'm sorry.

1050
01:32:01,857 --> 01:32:03,791
All right. Look.

1051
01:32:06,062 --> 01:32:08,587
I ran those phone records,
like you asked.

1052
01:32:08,664 --> 01:32:11,792
Could've meant my job,
but I did it.

1053
01:32:11,867 --> 01:32:14,199
Two telephone calls that Friday--
one from me...

1054
01:32:14,270 --> 01:32:18,331
and another from a pay phone
out Route 180, Pine Glenn outlets.

1055
01:32:18,407 --> 01:32:19,738
Pine Glenn?

1056
01:32:21,043 --> 01:32:24,535
A telephone call from your neighbor.
Nothing.

1057
01:32:30,953 --> 01:32:32,887
Talk to me, Michael.

1058
01:32:34,256 --> 01:32:36,190
What's going on?

1059
01:32:38,494 --> 01:32:40,428
Talk to me.

1060
01:32:48,370 --> 01:32:50,304
Give up the goddamn class.

1061
01:32:56,979 --> 01:32:59,345
I'd like to rent a car
tomorrow morning.

1062
01:32:59,415 --> 01:33:01,781
How early could I pick that up?

1063
01:33:04,420 --> 01:33:06,354
Michael Faraday.

1064
01:33:49,698 --> 01:33:51,097
Oliver Lang, please.

1065
01:33:51,167 --> 01:33:53,567
Mr. Lang is out of the office.
Would you like to leave a message?

1066
01:33:53,636 --> 01:33:55,627
I need to reach him.
This is a business emergency.

1067
01:33:55,704 --> 01:33:58,935
Mr. Lang isn't expected in this morning.

1068
01:33:59,008 --> 01:34:01,408
- I'll call back. Thanks.
- Is there something else--

1069
01:34:01,477 --> 01:34:03,672
No.

1070
01:37:56,712 --> 01:38:01,172
Hey, neighbor, you all right?
What you doin' on this side of town?

1071
01:38:04,119 --> 01:38:06,587
Had to know, didn't ya?
Had to know.

1072
01:38:06,655 --> 01:38:09,215
Couldn't leave your neighbor alone.

1073
01:38:24,206 --> 01:38:26,231
Didn't you check up on me?

1074
01:38:26,308 --> 01:38:28,333
Didn't you?

1075
01:38:28,410 --> 01:38:31,004
Did you really think
we'd leave anything to chance?

1076
01:38:31,079 --> 01:38:33,513
Fifty-one.

1077
01:38:33,582 --> 01:38:36,813
I've got your shadow.
Go ahead. We're still on schedule.

1078
01:38:40,556 --> 01:38:43,286
- You gonna miss your son, Michael?
- Please.

1079
01:38:43,358 --> 01:38:46,384
You've given me no choice!

1080
01:38:46,462 --> 01:38:50,398
You think I wanted this?
I told you you were gonna get him back!

1081
01:38:50,466 --> 01:38:53,902
How am I gonna do that now?
How am I gonna trust you now?

1082
01:38:53,969 --> 01:38:56,961
Where are you taking him?
Where's the bomb?

1083
01:39:00,242 --> 01:39:03,734
I'm a messenger, Michael.
I'm a messenger!

1084
01:39:03,812 --> 01:39:06,246
There's millions of us,
waiting to take up arms...

1085
01:39:06,315 --> 01:39:08,510
ready to spread the word.

1086
01:39:08,584 --> 01:39:09,915
Millions of us!

1087
01:39:09,985 --> 01:39:12,180
The government's
not who you're killing!

1088
01:39:12,254 --> 01:39:15,655
Yes, yes, they'll pay.
They'll pay for their sins...

1089
01:39:15,724 --> 01:39:17,521
- You're killing children !
- their lies, their children.

1090
01:39:17,593 --> 01:39:19,322
- Children die!
- This is war.

1091
01:39:19,394 --> 01:39:21,589
In a war, children die.

1092
01:39:21,663 --> 01:39:23,858
- You're with us!
- No!

1093
01:39:46,688 --> 01:39:49,555
Liberty Two, status.

1094
01:39:50,893 --> 01:39:52,554
Status one, go.

1095
01:39:52,628 --> 01:39:55,722
That's what you stand for.

1096
01:39:55,797 --> 01:39:59,164
You tell them you stand for
blowing up families...

1097
01:39:59,234 --> 01:40:01,168
for orphan sons.

1098
01:40:02,938 --> 01:40:06,567
Your father really kill himself,
you son of a bitch?

1099
01:40:06,642 --> 01:40:08,735
Or is that just one of your
goddamn stories?

1100
01:40:10,312 --> 01:40:13,713
- Call it oft!
- It's for you, Michael.

1101
01:40:13,782 --> 01:40:15,841
- It's for all of us.
- It's not for me. Call it oft!

1102
01:40:16,985 --> 01:40:19,977
Are you happy in your godless,
suburban life?

1103
01:40:20,055 --> 01:40:22,421
Call oft the bomb!

1104
01:40:22,491 --> 01:40:25,324
Call off the fuckin' bomb!

1105
01:40:29,231 --> 01:40:31,358
They sent your wife
to her death.

1106
01:40:31,433 --> 01:40:34,402
Surely you won't be sorry
to see them go.

1107
01:40:41,677 --> 01:40:43,269
You're too late!

1108
01:41:16,645 --> 01:41:18,636
Let's get it done.

1109
01:41:28,857 --> 01:41:30,256
- Agent Carver.
- Listen to me.

1110
01:41:30,325 --> 01:41:34,386
There's a bomb on its way
to your offices. Get everybody out!

1111
01:41:34,463 --> 01:41:36,658
- What's going on?
- It's in a white van.

1112
01:41:36,732 --> 01:41:39,064
A Liberty Delivery Van.
Grant's in there.

1113
01:41:41,637 --> 01:41:43,571
They want the FBI this time!

1114
01:41:43,639 --> 01:41:46,005
Michael, you're breaking up!

1115
01:41:47,409 --> 01:41:49,775
Whit? Shit!

1116
01:41:54,549 --> 01:41:56,847
Come on !

1117
01:42:09,831 --> 01:42:11,526
Security, main gate.

1118
01:43:03,585 --> 01:43:05,314
Out of the way!

1119
01:43:57,139 --> 01:43:59,403
That's the van!

1120
01:43:59,474 --> 01:44:01,965
Stop it!

1121
01:44:06,214 --> 01:44:08,944
- Stop the van!
- Sir, step out of the vehicle!

1122
01:44:09,017 --> 01:44:12,783
- There's a bomb in the van !
- Step out of the vehicle!

1123
01:44:12,854 --> 01:44:15,322
- It's got a goddamn bomb!
- Michael, wait!

1124
01:44:15,390 --> 01:44:18,553
That's the van!
There's a bomb in there!

1125
01:44:18,627 --> 01:44:21,653
- That van was authorized.
- That's the van! Grant's inside!

1126
01:44:21,730 --> 01:44:24,164
It's the noon delivery.

1127
01:44:26,401 --> 01:44:28,665
Grant's in there!
It's got a goddamn bomb!

1128
01:44:38,380 --> 01:44:39,847
Hold your tire!

1129
01:44:55,463 --> 01:44:58,955
- Don't shoot!
- In the van!

1130
01:45:02,671 --> 01:45:06,300
Get everyone out of the building!
There's a bomb in the van !

1131
01:45:12,681 --> 01:45:15,650
- Get him out of the building.
- Check the goddamn van.

1132
01:45:18,720 --> 01:45:21,188
We gotta get everybody out of here.
There's a bomb.

1133
01:45:21,256 --> 01:45:23,190
- It's in there.
- Easy.

1134
01:45:26,561 --> 01:45:28,028
Wait! That's--

1135
01:45:28,096 --> 01:45:30,860
That's not the man.

1136
01:45:30,932 --> 01:45:33,298
- All right.
- Grant!

1137
01:45:34,836 --> 01:45:36,303
Let him go.

1138
01:45:36,371 --> 01:45:38,635
I said, let him go!

1139
01:45:39,641 --> 01:45:42,166
- Back off!
- The van's clean.

1140
01:45:42,244 --> 01:45:44,838
There's nothing in here.

1141
01:45:44,913 --> 01:45:47,848
Go ahead, Michael.

1142
01:46:00,996 --> 01:46:03,396
Michael, it's all clear.

1143
01:46:03,465 --> 01:46:06,332
The guy's authorized to be here.

1144
01:46:06,401 --> 01:46:10,565
We're all authorized to be here.
Everyone except you.

1145
01:46:13,775 --> 01:46:16,835
All right? Come on.

1146
01:46:22,183 --> 01:46:24,378
It's all right.

1147
01:46:39,834 --> 01:46:41,267
Hey, guys!

1148
01:47:00,555 --> 01:47:02,113
Stand by.

1149
01:47:38,660 --> 01:47:40,890
Everyone except you.

1150
01:47:53,575 --> 01:47:55,008
Boom.

1151
01:48:29,477 --> 01:48:32,310
Right now, I'm sort of breathless.

1152
01:48:32,380 --> 01:48:34,814
I've just gotten here,
and there are people lying--

1153
01:48:54,302 --> 01:48:56,770
It looks just like a war zone!

1154
01:49:09,918 --> 01:49:12,614
Officials at this point believe
a bomb went off.

1155
01:49:12,687 --> 01:49:15,247
They're not sure
which floor, how big.

1156
01:49:15,323 --> 01:49:19,885
Obviously, it was massive
to create the kind of devastation--

1157
01:49:54,262 --> 01:49:56,628
Preliminary reports indicate
the bombing was the work...

1158
01:49:56,698 --> 01:50:00,293
of this man, Michael Faraday
of Reston, Virginia.

1159
01:50:00,368 --> 01:50:03,462
A professor of history
at George Washington University--

1160
01:50:03,538 --> 01:50:07,338
Officials will not confirm reports
that the bombing had anything to do...

1161
01:50:07,408 --> 01:50:11,742
with the death of Mr. Faraday's wife,
who had been an FBI agent.

1162
01:50:19,454 --> 01:50:21,888
Students and colleagues both say...

1163
01:50:21,956 --> 01:50:26,450
that Farady's behavior was increasingly
erratic in the weeks leading up--

1164
01:50:26,528 --> 01:50:30,089
He was really intense, you know?
Knew all about these terrorists--

1165
01:50:30,165 --> 01:50:32,292
how they worked, what they wanted.

1166
01:50:32,367 --> 01:50:35,200
He was really into it.
It was my favorite class.

1167
01:50:35,270 --> 01:50:38,330
We went to this field trip once.
It was Copper Creek.

1168
01:50:38,406 --> 01:50:42,570
He practically broke down and started
crying, something about his wife.

1169
01:50:42,644 --> 01:50:45,807
We all sort of knew about it, but
he never really wanted to talk about it.

1170
01:50:48,016 --> 01:50:51,645
Faraday reportedly blamed the Bureau
for its role in his wife's death...

1171
01:50:51,719 --> 01:50:53,311
almost three years ago.

1172
01:50:53,388 --> 01:50:55,481
Specifically, sources
speculate his target...

1173
01:50:55,557 --> 01:51:00,722
may have been Agent Whit Carver, one of
the 184 people to perish in the attack.

1174
01:51:00,795 --> 01:51:04,060
Carver was a partner
of Faraday's wife at Copper Creek...

1175
01:51:04,132 --> 01:51:06,293
and Faraday
may have held him responsible.

1176
01:51:06,367 --> 01:51:10,394
All I know is what he told me
in his office one day after class.

1177
01:51:10,471 --> 01:51:12,962
I'll never forget that.

1178
01:51:13,041 --> 01:51:16,204
He said, "Sweetheart...

1179
01:51:16,277 --> 01:51:19,474
one day those men are going to pay.

1180
01:51:19,547 --> 01:51:22,277
One day those men
are going to burn. "

1181
01:51:32,894 --> 01:51:37,160
Yet all of them described Faraday
as solitary but friendly...

1182
01:51:37,232 --> 01:51:41,293
as a talented professor fascinated
by the American underground...

1183
01:51:41,369 --> 01:51:44,532
and as a loving father
to his ten-year-old son...

1184
01:51:44,606 --> 01:51:46,836
who is now in the care of relatives.

1185
01:51:53,248 --> 01:51:57,344
And so after exhausting hundreds
of thousands of man-hours and leads...

1186
01:51:57,418 --> 01:52:00,216
federal investigators are finally
ready to say...

1187
01:52:00,288 --> 01:52:04,247
that just as in the St. Louis
IRS bombing nearly two years ago...

1188
01:52:04,325 --> 01:52:06,657
this spring's attack on the FBl...

1189
01:52:06,728 --> 01:52:09,219
the worst terrorist strike
in our nation's history...

1190
01:52:09,297 --> 01:52:12,357
was the work of one man
and one man alone.

1191
01:52:17,672 --> 01:52:19,663
Any news yet?

1192
01:52:19,741 --> 01:52:22,801
No. They'll let us know.

1193
01:52:26,080 --> 01:52:28,310
Someplace nice.

1194
01:52:28,383 --> 01:52:29,975
I hope.

1195
01:52:31,419 --> 01:52:33,011
Someplace sate.

1196
01:52:35,456 --> 01:52:37,048
Always.

